title Stale detection works via edges, not history walking
edge applies-to blob:4b7d34961946b4e09ebe8e2e752e67b5b76c13db
edge targets-path path:mycelium.sh

The three sessions designed applies-to + targets-path edges specifically
so staleness could be detected by comparing the stored blob OID against
the current blob at that path. This works: no git log walking needed.
context and read both surface [stale] notes when the blob changes.

Scenario results:
- Stale blob: read shows [stale] with the old note. Works.
- Amend without rewriteRef: note orphans silently. Git-native fix: notes.rewriteRef.
- Amend WITH rewriteRef: note follows. But edge still has old commit OID (cosmetic).
- Deep tree inheritance: constraint on src/auth/ surfaces for src/auth/providers/oauth/refresh.ts. Works.
- File rename without content change: blob OID unchanged, note follows automatically. Surprise win.
- File rename old path: errors (file gone). Path edge becomes stale but note still findable via dump/find.
